gomodel:SYNGO_1010  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" , "Rationale: The location of the adenosine A2A receptor was assessed by pre-embedding immunoperoxidase and immunogold labelling. The A2A receptor was found in dendrites and spines (Table1 and 2, Fig.2-6). Immunoreactivity was found on plasma membranes and endomembranes.\n\nA monoclonal, mouse, antiserum was raised against the human adenosine A2A receptor (clone 7F6-G5-A2, Upstate USA, Charlotteswville, VA). The antibody produced the same immunoreactivity pattern in wildtype mice, but not in A2A KO mice (data not shown in this paper).. Experimental description: Six adult male Sprague-Dawleyrats (200-250 g; Taconic Farms, Germantown, NY) weredeeply anesthetized by..." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
